{
  "answer": "To derive the first-order conditions for the FIML estimator, we start with the loglikelihood function (12.107):\\nStep 1: Write down the loglikelihood function explicitly:\\\\\\ \\\\-\\frac{g n}{2}(\\log2\\pi+1)+\\sum_{t=1}^{n}\\log|\\operatorname*{det}J_{t}|-\\frac{n}{2}\\log\\Big|\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{t=1}^{n}h_{t}^{\\top}(Y_{t},\\theta)h_{t}(Y_{t},\\theta)\\Big|.\\\\\\\\nStep 2: Differentiate the loglikelihood function with respect to the parameter vector \\(\\theta\\). This involves differentiating each term separately.\\\\\\ \\\\-\\frac{g n}{2}(\\log2\\pi+1): This term is constant with respect to \\(\\theta\\), so its derivative is zero.\\\\\\\\nStep 3: Differentiate the second term \\(\\sum_{t=1}^{n}\\log|\\operatorname*{det}J_{t}|\\) with respect to \\(\\theta\\). Using the chain rule, the derivative is:\\\\\\[\\sum_{t=1}^{n} \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\theta} \\log |\\operatorname*{det} J_t| = \\sum_{t=1}^{n} \\operatorname*{tr}(J_t^{-1} \\frac{\\partial J_t}{\\partial \\theta}).\\\\\\\\nStep 4: Differentiate the third term \\(-\\frac{n}{2}\\log\\Big|\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{t=1}^{n}h_{t}^{\\top}(Y_{t},\\theta)h_{t}(Y_{t},\\theta)\\Big|\\) with respect to \\(\\theta\\). Using the chain rule, the derivative is:\\\\\\[ -\\frac{n}{2} \\cdot \\frac{1}{\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{t=1}^{n}h_{t}^{\\top}(Y_{t},\\theta)h_{t}(Y_{t},\\theta)} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\theta} \\Big(\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{t=1}^{n}h_{t}^{\\top}(Y_{t},\\theta)h_{t}(Y_{t},\\theta)\\Big).\\\\\\\\nStep 5: Combine all the derivatives to obtain the first-order conditions. The first-order conditions require setting the derivative of the loglikelihood function with respect to \\(\\theta\\) equal to zero:\\\\\\[\\sum_{t=1}^{n} \\operatorname*{tr}(J_t^{-1} \\frac{\\partial J_t}{\\partial \\theta}) - \\frac{n}{2} \\cdot \\frac{1}{\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{t=1}^{n}h_{t}^{\\top}(Y_{t},\\theta)h_{t}(Y_{t},\\theta)} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial \\theta} \\Big(\\frac{1}{n}\\sum_{t=1}^{n}h_{t}^{\\top}(Y_{t},\\theta)h_{t}(Y_{t},\\theta)\\Big) = 0.\\\\\\\\nThus, the first-order conditions for the FIML estimator are given by the above equation."
}

