  "answer": "Step 1: Deriving the OLS Estimator for the Model \\\\( colGPA = \\beta_0 + \\beta_1 alcohol + \\beta_2 hsGPA + \\beta_3 SAT + \\beta_4 female + u \\\\):\\nTo derive the Ordinary Least Squares (OLS) estimator, we minimize the sum of squared residuals. Let the residual be defined as \\\\( e_i = y_i - \\hat{y}_i = y_i - (\\hat{\\beta}_0 + \\hat{\\beta}_1 x_{i1} + \\hat{\\beta}_2 x_{i2} + \\hat{\\beta}_3 x_{i3} + \\hat{\\beta}_4 x_{i4}) \\\\), where \\\\( y_i \\\\) is the observed dependent variable and \\\\( x_{ij} \\\\) are the independent variables.\\nThe objective function to minimize is:\\\\[ S(\\beta_0, \\beta_1, \\beta_2, \\beta_3, \\beta_4) = \\sum_{i=1}^n e_i^2 = \\sum_{i=1}^n (y_i - \\beta_0 - \\beta_1 x_{i1} - \\beta_2 x_{i2} - \\beta_3 x_{i3} - \\beta_4 x_{i4})^2 \\\\.\\nTaking partial derivatives with respect to each coefficient and setting them equal to zero yields the normal equations:\\\\[ \\frac{\\partial S}{\\partial \\beta_0} = -2 \\sum_{i=1}^n (y_i - \\beta_0 - \\beta_1 x_{i1} - \\beta_2 x_{i2} - \\beta_3 x_{i3} - \\beta_4 x_{i4}) = 0 \\\\,\\\\[ \\frac{\\partial S}{\\partial \\beta_1} = -2 \\sum_{i=1}^n x_{i1} (y_i - \\beta_0 - \\beta_1 x_{i1} - \\beta_2 x_{i2} - \\beta_3 x_{i3} - \\beta_4 x_{i4}) = 0 \\\\,\\\\[ \\frac{\\partial S}{\\partial \\beta_2} = -2 \\sum_{i=1}^n x_{i2} (y_i - \\beta_0 - \\beta_1 x_{i1} - \\beta_2 x_{i2} - \\beta_3 x_{i3} - \\beta_4 x_{i4}) = 0 \\\\,\\\\[ \\frac{\\partial S}{\\partial \\beta_3} = -2 \\sum_{i=1}^n x_{i3} (y_i - \\beta_0 - \\beta_1 x_{i1} - \\beta_2 x_{i2} - \\beta_3 x_{i3} - \\beta_4 x_{i4}) = 0 \\\\,\\\\[ \\frac{\\partial S}{\\partial \\beta_4} = -2 \\sum_{i=1}^n x_{i4} (y_i - \\beta_0 - \\beta_1 x_{i1} - \\beta_2 x_{i2} - \\beta_3 x_{i3} - \\beta_4 x_{i4}) = 0 \\\\.\\nSolving these equations simultaneously provides the OLS estimators for the coefficients.\\nStep 2: Assumptions Required for OLS to Be BLUE (Best Linear Unbiased Estimator):\\\\\\n1. Linearity: The relationship between the dependent variable and the independent variables is linear in parameters.\\\\\\n2. Random Sampling: Observations are independently and identically distributed (i.i.d.).\\\\\\[3. Zero Conditional Mean: E(u|X) = 0, meaning the error term has zero mean conditional on the independent variables.\\\\\\[4. Homoscedasticity: Var(u|X) = \\sigma^2, meaning the variance of the error term is constant across observations.\\\\\\[5. No Perfect Multicollinearity: None of the independent variables are perfectly collinear.\\\\\\[6. Normality of Errors (optional for finite sample properties but necessary for hypothesis testing): u ~ N(0, \\sigma^2)."
